The paper discusses citation analysis and bibliometric indicators, which are commonly used in the field of computer science to evaluate research impact. The methodology used in the paper involves extracting terms from titles and abstracts of publications, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses differences in citation practices between research areas, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as social and information networks (cs.SI), computational biology (cs.CY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
